WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.668
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.205 --> 00:06.872
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.541
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.576 --> 00:11.743
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.845
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.880 --> 00:16.181
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.216 --> 00:17.516
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:19.217
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.252 --> 00:20.853
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:22.089 --> 00:25.590
♪♪

00:25.625 --> 00:28.127
[ Funky music plays ]

00:32.699 --> 00:33.765
Ugh!

00:33.800 --> 00:36.001
It's too hot
to focus on this!

00:36.036 --> 00:38.170
Ice Bear must keep cool.

00:38.205 --> 00:41.173
Ice Bear must keep cool.

00:41.208 --> 00:42.941
Ugh.
Come on, Kirk.

00:42.976 --> 00:44.943
Do something cute
for our selfie!

00:44.978 --> 00:46.011
[ Whimpers ]

00:46.046 --> 00:48.013
Ugh!
Never mind.

00:48.048 --> 00:50.549
Can we eat now?
I'm so hungry.

00:50.584 --> 00:53.285
Patience, stripes!
You cant rush perfection.

00:53.320 --> 00:56.388
All right.
Let's do this!

00:56.423 --> 00:57.923
[ Grunting ]

00:57.958 --> 00:59.925
[ Action music plays ]

00:59.960 --> 01:01.293
Ha!

01:06.933 --> 01:09.701
Behold my culinary masterpiece!

01:09.736 --> 01:10.969
Huh?!           Huh?!

01:11.004 --> 01:13.438
Er, check out
this sandwich I made.

01:13.473 --> 01:15.207
Oh!
- A sandwich, that's neat.

01:15.242 --> 01:16.541
I love sandwiches.

01:16.576 --> 01:18.310
That's right.
Feast your eyes!

01:18.345 --> 01:19.711
Isn't it
the most beautiful

01:19.746 --> 01:21.046
sandwich
you've ever seen?

01:21.081 --> 01:22.314
Oh,
is that avocado?

01:22.349 --> 01:23.715
Wow,
it's really square!

01:23.750 --> 01:25.917
Ice Bear thinks square
is most delicious shape.

01:25.952 --> 01:27.285
Yep, a perfect
right angle --

01:27.320 --> 01:28.453
just like Mom
used to make.

01:28.488 --> 01:30.222
All right, guys,
let's eat!

01:30.257 --> 01:31.590
-Yeah!
-Whoo-hoo!

01:31.625 --> 01:32.657
[ Kirk barking ]

01:32.692 --> 01:34.793
Aww. Do you need
to go outside, boy?

01:34.828 --> 01:36.461
Well, I guess lunch
can wait a few minutes.

01:36.496 --> 01:38.497
Better put this
in the fridge for now

01:38.532 --> 01:41.200
to keep it at the optimal
food safety temperature.

01:43.637 --> 01:46.238
Okay, guys,
I'll be right back!

01:46.273 --> 01:49.441
Martinez, you're in charge
while I'm gone.

01:49.476 --> 01:50.575
[ Snoring ]

01:50.610 --> 01:52.410
Great work, Martinez!

01:52.445 --> 01:55.914
[ Kirk barking ] Whoa!
Oh, okay, bye, guys!

01:55.949 --> 01:58.016
Um, I guess we'll wait?

01:58.051 --> 01:59.451
Aw, man!

01:59.486 --> 02:01.487
[ Clock ticking ]

02:05.125 --> 02:08.127
[ Snores ]

02:08.862 --> 02:10.195
I'm back!
- Aah!

02:10.230 --> 02:11.863
Kirk and I really worked up
an appetite out there.

02:11.898 --> 02:14.633
Come on, guys,
let's get this lunch starte--

02:14.668 --> 02:15.834
[ Gasps ]

02:15.869 --> 02:17.302
♪♪

02:17.337 --> 02:19.204
Wha?
Wha?!

02:19.239 --> 02:20.305
What's wrong, Tabes?

02:20.340 --> 02:22.607
What's wrong?
Can't you tell?

02:22.642 --> 02:25.610
Don't you see
what's wrong here?!

02:25.645 --> 02:26.678
Oh, man.

02:26.713 --> 02:28.380
Someone took your sandwich?
That's rough.

02:28.415 --> 02:29.948
Oh, yeah.
I'm sorry, Tabes.

02:29.983 --> 02:31.216
Ice Bear will help make
new sandwich.

02:31.251 --> 02:32.484
Hey, good idea, bro!

02:32.519 --> 02:34.052
We'll all help you make
a new one!

02:34.087 --> 02:35.453
A new one?!

02:35.488 --> 02:36.788
You know how hard I worked
on that sandwich!

02:36.823 --> 02:38.957
I put my blood, tears,
and sweat into it!

02:38.992 --> 02:39.958
Ew!

02:39.993 --> 02:41.159
And now it's been taken

02:41.194 --> 02:44.329
before I even got
to taste it!

02:44.364 --> 02:45.297
No.

02:45.332 --> 02:46.531
I refuse to trivialize
this crime

02:46.566 --> 02:49.234
by simply making
a new sandwich.

02:49.269 --> 02:51.503
Justice must be served!

02:51.538 --> 02:54.806
Uh, can justice wait
until after lunch is served?

02:54.841 --> 02:55.974
No,
it can't wait!

02:56.009 --> 02:57.309
Justice
never sleeps...

02:57.344 --> 03:00.912
or eats or...goes
to the bathroom.

03:00.947 --> 03:02.380
Hey, we'll help you
figure it out

03:02.415 --> 03:03.982
if it means
we can eat sooner.

03:04.017 --> 03:05.317
Excellent!

03:05.352 --> 03:06.418
First, we'll need
to question the suspects.

03:06.453 --> 03:07.852
Right!
Suspects!

03:07.887 --> 03:09.588
Um, who are they?

03:09.623 --> 03:11.723
Isn't it obvious,
my dear Grizz?

03:11.758 --> 03:15.527
The sandwich was eaten
while I was outside with Kirk.

03:15.562 --> 03:16.361
Which means...

03:16.396 --> 03:17.596
Oh!
I know, I know!

03:17.631 --> 03:20.398
That means
- that the thief was...inside?

03:20.433 --> 03:21.933
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my gosh!

03:21.968 --> 03:23.268
What if he's still here?!

03:23.303 --> 03:25.570
[ Sighs ]
<i>We're</i> the suspects, Grizz.

03:25.605 --> 03:26.571
Bingo.

03:26.606 --> 03:30.375
Ice Bear has committed
no crime...today.

03:31.811 --> 03:35.214
♪♪

03:37.217 --> 03:38.850
[ Panda whimpering ]

03:38.885 --> 03:40.352
Ahh! - What's the
matter, Stripes?

03:40.387 --> 03:41.686
Nervous?
Feeling guilty?

03:41.721 --> 03:44.522
Don't worry.
- You'll have your chance to talk.

03:44.557 --> 03:48.260
But, first,
where were you, Martinez?!

03:48.295 --> 03:50.895
[ Snoring ]

03:50.930 --> 03:52.931
Hmm.
Pretty strong alibi.

03:52.966 --> 03:53.965
Grizzly!

03:54.000 --> 03:54.966
Uh, I didn't do it!

03:55.001 --> 03:56.301
I swear I'm innocent!

03:56.336 --> 03:57.535
I'm listening.

03:57.570 --> 03:59.037
Um, okay,
I was waiting

03:59.072 --> 04:00.905
for you to come back
from your walk.

04:00.940 --> 04:02.240
I was playing
with my blocks

04:02.275 --> 04:04.809
when something flew past
the window outside!

04:04.844 --> 04:06.278
I had to investigate,

04:06.313 --> 04:08.880
but Martinez was asleep
in front of the window.

04:08.915 --> 04:12.550
So I, uh, gracefully moved
around him and climbed out.

04:12.585 --> 04:14.052
Oof!

04:14.087 --> 04:15.820
It was a totally sweet
boomerang,

04:15.855 --> 04:17.389
but it was stuck
in the bug zapper.

04:17.424 --> 04:18.757
I mean, I really wanted
to rescue it, but...

04:18.792 --> 04:20.058
Aah!

04:20.093 --> 04:22.761
...every time I tried
to grab it, I'd get zapped!

04:22.796 --> 04:23.895
Aah!

04:23.930 --> 04:26.898
So I knew I had to devise
a clever plan.

04:26.933 --> 04:27.899
Sneak attack!

04:27.934 --> 04:29.234
Aah!
Oof!

04:29.269 --> 04:32.771
Using a stick, I carefully
disabled the zapper,

04:32.806 --> 04:35.073
finally allowing me to pull
the boomerang to safety.

04:35.108 --> 04:37.075
Hyah!
Ha!

04:37.110 --> 04:38.510
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

04:38.545 --> 04:40.245
But it turned out
- that disabling the bug zapper

04:40.280 --> 04:41.479
was a bad idea.

04:41.514 --> 04:42.580
I mean, suddenly,
I was surrounded

04:42.615 --> 04:44.582
by, like, a zillion bugs.

04:44.617 --> 04:46.084
I tried to fight them off
with my boomerang,

04:46.119 --> 04:47.352
but they just kept
coming!

04:47.387 --> 04:49.821
Ugh! I think I even got one
in my mouth.

04:49.856 --> 04:51.423
Eventually, I made it back
to the station,

04:51.458 --> 04:52.824
locking the bugs outside.

04:52.859 --> 04:54.592
Pbht! Aah!

04:54.627 --> 04:57.195
And, safely inside,
I returned to my blocks,

04:57.230 --> 04:59.097
which I'm awesome at.

04:59.132 --> 05:01.433
Hmm.
Good story.

05:01.468 --> 05:04.002
But if it's true,
- then where's the boomerang?

05:04.037 --> 05:05.036
Well...

05:05.071 --> 05:06.771
Save me, boomerang!

05:06.806 --> 05:08.773
[ Grunts ]

05:08.808 --> 05:10.342
[ Ting! ]

05:10.377 --> 05:12.110
But it never came back.

05:12.145 --> 05:13.712
Hmm. Okay.

05:13.747 --> 05:17.115
Guess that checks out...
for now.

05:17.150 --> 05:18.149
Stripes!
- Aah!

05:18.184 --> 05:19.551
What's your story?

05:19.586 --> 05:21.386
Uh, so,
I was looking for something

05:21.421 --> 05:24.356
to make my profile stand out
more on my dating app.

05:24.391 --> 05:27.292
I just needed the perfect prop.

05:27.327 --> 05:29.327
[ Funky music plays ]

05:29.362 --> 05:31.196
And then I saw it.

05:31.231 --> 05:33.131
[ Sparkle! ]
Bingo!

05:33.166 --> 05:35.300
Ladies love a man in uniform.

05:35.335 --> 05:38.136
I politely asked
to borrow Martinez's hat.

05:38.171 --> 05:39.237
Martinez?
- Hmm?

05:39.272 --> 05:40.739
Can I --
Can I borrow your hat?

05:40.774 --> 05:43.641
[ Snores softly ]
Ma-- Martinez?

05:43.676 --> 05:45.343
I'm gonna take that
as a yes.

05:45.378 --> 05:46.978
[ Giggles ]

05:47.013 --> 05:48.813
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
I then took a few selfies...

05:48.848 --> 05:50.248
I like this hat.

05:50.283 --> 05:52.150
...and then,
I went to return the hat.

05:52.185 --> 05:54.352
[ Snoring ]

05:54.387 --> 05:56.888
But Martinez
was making things difficult.

05:56.923 --> 05:58.890
[ Grunting ]

05:58.925 --> 06:00.692
Oh, come on, man!

06:00.727 --> 06:02.694
What, what?!

06:02.729 --> 06:03.895
Hmm?

06:03.930 --> 06:04.929
Eh.

06:04.964 --> 06:06.364
[ Snoring resumes ]

06:06.399 --> 06:08.199
And then
I just lied on the floor

06:08.234 --> 06:10.201
and tried to stay cool.

06:10.236 --> 06:12.170
Fair enough.

06:12.205 --> 06:13.571
[ Sighs ]
- What was that?!

06:13.606 --> 06:15.440
Nothing, nothing!
It was nothing!

06:15.475 --> 06:18.009
What's your story?

06:18.044 --> 06:19.344
Yes, you.

06:19.379 --> 06:20.779
Ice Bear was on computer,

06:20.814 --> 06:22.914
researching the flowing stream
kung fu technique.

06:22.949 --> 06:24.516
[ Smooth jazz plays ]

06:24.551 --> 06:27.786
But then Ice Bear decided
to wash hands before lunch.

06:27.821 --> 06:29.387
Ice Bear walked
around sleeping Martinez

06:29.422 --> 06:30.889
to get to the bathroom.

06:32.258 --> 06:34.459
Ice Bear washed hands.

06:34.494 --> 06:36.294
Ice Bear dried hands.

06:36.329 --> 06:38.730
Ice Bear tried to leave,
but door handle was old.

06:39.732 --> 06:41.533
Ice Bear was trapped.
[ Doorknob clatters ]

06:41.568 --> 06:43.435
Ice Bear thought about
water dragon technique.

06:43.470 --> 06:46.137
[ Water bubbles, drips ]

06:46.172 --> 06:49.274
♪♪

06:52.145 --> 06:53.945
[ Rapid punching ]

06:55.949 --> 06:57.982
After mastering
water dragon technique,

06:58.017 --> 07:00.552
Ice Bear went back to computer
and watched cat videos.

07:00.587 --> 07:01.786
[<i> Growls</i> ]

07:01.821 --> 07:03.288
Ha ha.

07:03.323 --> 07:05.323
That is end of Ice Bear's tale.

07:05.358 --> 07:06.591
Solid alibi.

07:06.626 --> 07:10.261
Tabes: Interesting.
Very interesting.

07:10.296 --> 07:11.963
[ Gasps ]
I've got it!

07:11.998 --> 07:13.498
I know who the thief is!

07:13.533 --> 07:16.334
It was almost too easy.

07:16.369 --> 07:17.902
First, in Grizz's story,

07:17.937 --> 07:20.071
he allegedly climbed over
a sleeping Martinez

07:20.106 --> 07:22.674
to get out of the window
to find his boomerang.

07:22.709 --> 07:24.108
And then, in Panda's story,

07:24.143 --> 07:27.011
Martinez was clearly sleeping
at his desk

07:27.046 --> 07:28.613
when Panda borrowed his hat.

07:28.648 --> 07:30.815
And, lastly,
I recall a certain someone

07:30.850 --> 07:33.485
saying they had to move
around a sleeping Martinez

07:33.520 --> 07:35.086
to get to the bathroom.

07:35.121 --> 07:36.921
If all your stories are true,

07:36.956 --> 07:40.291
how was Martinez moving around
the station if he was asleep?

07:40.326 --> 07:41.593
He's a vampire!

07:41.628 --> 07:43.094
No, no, no, my friend.

07:43.129 --> 07:46.498
He wasn't sleeping!

07:46.533 --> 07:48.132
[ Snoring ]
[ Tabes clears throat ]

07:48.167 --> 07:49.167
Huh?

07:49.202 --> 07:50.969
Martinez?

07:51.004 --> 07:52.303
Hey, guys.

07:52.338 --> 07:53.838
Playing dumb, eh?

07:53.873 --> 07:56.441
Thought you'd eat my sandwich
and get away with it?!

07:56.476 --> 07:58.142
I-I didn't eat your lunch,
Tabes.

07:58.177 --> 07:59.344
I can't.

07:59.379 --> 08:01.546
I'm on this
gluten-free vegan diet.

08:01.581 --> 08:03.482
Check my top drawer.

08:04.884 --> 08:06.451
[ Gasps ]

08:06.486 --> 08:07.986
Sorry for doubting you,
Martinez.

08:08.021 --> 08:10.121
No one would eat kale chips
willingly.

08:10.156 --> 08:11.356
As you were.

08:11.391 --> 08:13.291
[ Snoring resumes ]

08:13.326 --> 08:14.959
But if Martinez was asleep,

08:14.994 --> 08:16.628
why was he moving
around the station?

08:16.663 --> 08:18.796
Um, Tabes, you mind
if I turn the fan back on?

08:18.831 --> 08:20.131
It's, like,
so hot in here.

08:20.166 --> 08:21.766
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, sure.
- Sweet.

08:24.704 --> 08:26.804
[ Chair wheels squeaking ]

08:26.839 --> 08:28.973
Ice Bear questions
physics involved.

08:29.008 --> 08:31.142
Well, I guess
that's one mystery solved.

08:31.177 --> 08:32.810
But one still remains!

08:32.845 --> 08:35.580
If Martinez isn't the culprit
and you all have alibis...

08:35.615 --> 08:37.015
I'm sorry, Tabes.

08:37.050 --> 08:38.816
Looks like this will just be
another unsolved mystery.

08:38.851 --> 08:42.387
No, Grizz.
- No mystery should go unsolved!

08:42.422 --> 08:44.222
Ah, think, Tabes, think!

08:45.024 --> 08:46.724
Well, I think
- if there's one culprit here,

08:46.759 --> 08:48.660
it's you, Pan Pan!
What?!

08:48.695 --> 08:51.162
Yeah, you're the one who said,
"I love avocado!"

08:51.197 --> 08:52.697
That's ridiculous!

08:52.732 --> 08:54.699
Besides, you're the one who said
you liked squared food!

08:54.734 --> 08:56.534
Nuh-uh!
That was this guy.

08:56.569 --> 08:58.336
Yeah, it was you!

08:58.371 --> 08:59.504
Ice Bear denies
your evidence.

08:59.539 --> 09:01.706
A likely story,
you selfish bear!

09:01.741 --> 09:03.041
He's not selfish.

09:03.076 --> 09:05.009
You're the one with all
the selfies, you weirdo!

09:05.044 --> 09:07.712
I said "selfish,"
not "selfie," ya dingle!

09:07.747 --> 09:09.614
[ Gasps ]
Selfies!

09:09.649 --> 09:11.516
Quick, Panda,
give me your phone!

09:11.551 --> 09:12.850
Huh?
My phone?

09:12.885 --> 09:14.052
Sure.

09:14.087 --> 09:15.687
And if anyone ate the sandwich,
it was you!

09:15.722 --> 09:16.688
Just look at you!

09:16.723 --> 09:17.789
Grizz: Uh, excuse me.

09:17.824 --> 09:19.023
What is that supposed to mean?

09:19.058 --> 09:20.058
]
s

09:20.093 --> 09:21.025
Huh?
Huh?            Huh?ed to mean?

09:21.060 --> 09:23.695
Bears,
I have solved the case

09:23.730 --> 09:24.963
for the second time.

09:24.998 --> 09:26.197
You see, I noticed

09:26.232 --> 09:27.599
that Kirk wanted to go out,

09:27.634 --> 09:29.434
so we left the ranger station
for a quick walk.

09:29.469 --> 09:32.136
In the woods, I let Kirk off
his leash to do his business.

09:32.171 --> 09:33.605
[ Barking ]

09:33.640 --> 09:36.708
And then I proceeded
to get in some calisthenics.

09:36.743 --> 09:38.943
Many sets later, Kirk returned.

09:38.978 --> 09:41.980
Then we happily arrived back
at the station, ready to eat.

09:42.015 --> 09:45.583
But, alas, my beloved sandwich
was stolen!

09:45.618 --> 09:47.418
As impressive
as those push-ups are,

09:47.453 --> 09:48.586
we already knew all that.

09:48.621 --> 09:49.654
But don't you see, Grizz?

09:49.689 --> 09:50.922
While we were all distracted,

09:50.957 --> 09:52.890
someone crept quietly
into the room,

09:52.925 --> 09:55.893
used the hand towel
to open the door,

09:55.928 --> 09:59.731
snatched the sandwich,
and escaped undetected!

09:59.766 --> 10:02.967
Was it Grizz, fighting off bugs
with his boomerang?

10:03.002 --> 10:06.838
Or sweet Stripes, searching
for the perfect selfie?

10:06.873 --> 10:08.740
Or you, the slyest
of the bunch?

10:08.775 --> 10:11.242
Ice Bear's flattered
and nervous.

10:11.277 --> 10:14.579
The thief has been
right under our noses.

10:14.614 --> 10:16.914
Feast your eyes
on the culprit!

10:16.949 --> 10:18.449
Panda:
Buh. I look terrible.

10:18.484 --> 10:20.051
Just scroll forward.

10:21.487 --> 10:22.754
Huh?
- Huh?            Huh?

10:22.789 --> 10:25.624
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

10:29.295 --> 10:30.361
[ Gasps ]
- [ Gasps ]

10:30.396 --> 10:32.363
Kirk!
What a sneaky sneak!

10:32.398 --> 10:34.499
Ice Bear knew
whole time.

10:34.534 --> 10:36.968
[ Coughs ]

10:37.003 --> 10:40.438
I'd be mad if I wasn't
so dang impressed.

10:40.473 --> 10:41.673
Respect.

10:41.708 --> 10:43.307
Well, at least
the case is solved!

10:43.342 --> 10:45.343
Sorry for putting you guys
through all this.

10:45.378 --> 10:48.346
Hey! How about I take you out
for pizza to make up for it?

10:48.381 --> 10:49.380
My treat.

10:49.415 --> 10:50.481
Yeah, pizza!

10:50.516 --> 10:52.183
Let's not bring Kirk,
though.

10:53.553 --> 10:54.952
Ice Bear is interested
in black light.

10:54.987 --> 10:57.221
Well, Glamazon has a great deal
on them right now.

10:57.256 --> 10:58.489
Hey!

10:58.524 --> 11:00.458
[ Gasps ]
- Boomerang, you came back!

11:00.493 --> 11:02.093
[ Groans ]

11:03.562 --> 11:06.297
♪♪
